答案:
\begin{align*}
f(x)&=x(ax^{2}+bx - 2)=ax(x - x_1)(x - x_2)\\
\end{align*}
由韦达定理，$x_1x_2=-\frac{2}{a}<0$，故$a>0$.
又$x_1 + x_2 =-\frac{b}{a}<0$，所以$b>0$. 故选(A).

当$|a - b|\leq\frac{1}{2}$时，有$|f(a)-f(b)|\leq|a - b|\leq\frac{1}{2}$。
当$|a - b|>\frac{1}{2}$时，不妨设$0\leq a < b\leq 1$，则$b - a > \frac{1}{2}$。于是有
\begin{align*}
|f(a)-f(b)|&=|f(a)-f(0)+f(1)-f(b)|\\
&\leq|f(a)-f(0)|+|f(1)-f(b)|\\
&\leq|a - 0|+|1 - b|\\
&=1-(b - a)\\
&<\frac{1}{2}
\end{align*}
证毕。

\begin{align*}
(2x + y)^{2} &= \left(\frac{2}{\sqrt{3}} \cdot \sqrt{3}x + \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \cdot \sqrt{2}y\right)^{2}\\
&\leq \left[\left(\frac{2}{\sqrt{3}}\right)^{2} + \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\right)^{2}\right] \cdot \left[(\sqrt{3}x)^{2} + (\sqrt{2}y)^{2}\right] = 11
\end{align*}
当且仅当$\frac{\frac{2}{\sqrt{3}}}{\sqrt{3}x} = \frac{\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}}{\sqrt{2}y}$，即$x = \frac{4}{\sqrt{11}}$，$y = \frac{3}{\sqrt{11}}$或$x = -\frac{4}{\sqrt{11}}$，$y = -\frac{3}{\sqrt{11}}$时等号成立. 故$2x + y$的最大值为$\sqrt{11}$.

\begin{align*}
\lim_{x \to 0} \left(\frac{\arctan x}{x}\right)^{\frac{1}{\tan^{2}x}} &= e^{\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\ln \frac{\arctan x}{x}}{\tan^{2}x}} = e^{\lim_{x \to 0} \left(\frac{\frac{\arctan x}{x}-1}{\tan^{2}x}\right)} = e^{\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\arctan x - x}{x^{3}}} = e^{-\frac{1}{3}}
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
&\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sqrt{1 + \tan x} - \sqrt{1 + \sin x}}{x^2 - x\ln(1 + x)}\\
=&\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\tan x - \sin x}{x[x - \ln(1 + x)]} \cdot \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 + \tan x} + \sqrt{1 + \sin x}}\\
=&\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\tan x(1 - \cos x)}{x[x - \ln(1 + x)]} \cdot \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 + \tan x} + \sqrt{1 + \sin x}}\\
=&\frac{1}{2} \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{1 - \cos x}{x - \ln(1 + x)} = \frac{1}{2} \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin x}{1 - \frac{1}{1 + x}}\\
=&\frac{1}{2} \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{(1 + x)\sin x}{x} = \frac{1}{2}
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
&\text{原式}=\lim_{x \to +\infty} \left[\ln 2^{x} + \ln\left(1 + \frac{1}{2^{x}}\right)\right] \cdot \frac{2}{x}\\
=&\lim_{x \to +\infty} x\ln 2 \cdot \frac{2}{x} + \lim_{x \to +\infty} \frac{1}{2^{x}} \cdot \frac{2}{x}=2\ln 2
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
&\lim_{x \to \infty} \left(\cos \frac{1}{x} + \sin \frac{1}{x}\right)^{\frac{x}{2}} = \lim_{x \to \infty} \left[\left(\cos \frac{1}{x} + \sin \frac{1}{x}\right)^2\right]^{\frac{x}{4}}\\
=&\lim_{x \to \infty} \left(1 + \sin \frac{2}{x}\right)^{\frac{x}{4}}\\
=&\lim_{x \to \infty} \left(1 + \sin \frac{2}{x}\right)^{\frac{1}{\sin \frac{2}{x}} \cdot \sin \frac{2}{x} \cdot \frac{x}{4}}
\end{align*}
由于$\lim_{x \to \infty} \sin \frac{2}{x} \cdot \frac{x}{4} = \lim_{x \to \infty} \frac{\sin \frac{2}{x}}{\frac{4}{x}} = \frac{1}{2}$，因此原极限$=\sqrt{\mathrm{e}}$.

\begin{align*}
\lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{n^{99}}{n^{100} - (n - 1)^{100}} &= \lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{n^{99}}{n^{100} \left[1 - \left(1 - \frac{1}{n}\right)^{100}\right]}\\
&= - \lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{n^{99 - 100}}{\left(1 - \frac{1}{n}\right)^{100} - 1}\\
&= - \lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{\frac{1}{n}}{100 \left(- \frac{1}{n}\right)}\\
&= \frac{1}{100}
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
f_{+}'(0) &= \lim_{x \to 0^{+}} \frac{f(x) - f(0)}{x - 0} = \lim_{x \to 0^{+}} \frac{f(x)}{x}\\
\end{align*}
由$n^2 \leq \frac{1}{x} < (n + 1)^2$，得$\frac{n^2}{n^2} \leq \frac{f(x)}{x} < (\frac{n + 1}{n})^2$，当$x \to 0^{+}$时，$n \to \infty$，根据夹逼准则，$\lim_{x \to 0^{+}} \frac{f(x)}{x} = 1$，即$f_{+}'(0) = 1$。
